{"lemma": "لِجامٌ", "slug": "لِجامٌ", "root": "ل.ج.م", "root_slug": "ل-ج-م", "root_link": "/words/roots/ل-ج-م", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 1, "pos_tags": ["noun"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 2}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n43237"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%84%D9%90%D8%AC%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "bridle bit", "fa": "لجام", "ur": "لجام", "tr": "ağır", "id": "pelana", "bn": "লিগাম", "es": "bocado", "fr": "mors", "de": "Gebiss", "ru": "удила", "zh": "马嚼子"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "a bridle bit", "tags": ["archaic", "countable"]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "a horse headcollar or headstall along with the reins; a bridle", "tags": ["countable"]}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "From Classical Persian لگام (ligām) or from an identical rare Aramaic term, see there."}, "ipa": ["/li.d͡ʒaːm/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n43237", "headword_ar": "لِجَامٌ", "root": "ljm", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A bit;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e.,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the iron appurtenances of a bridle"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. To the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ljAm", "text_ar": "لجام"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "belong pieces of iron which are fastened one to another; as the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EiDaAdataAni", "text_ar": "عِضَادَتَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "misoHal", "text_ar": "مِسْحَل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faA^os", "text_ar": "فَاْس"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and its extremities of iron. (Az, in TA, voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qayoqabN", "text_ar": "قَيْقَبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) The above explanation is incomplete: it means the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "bridle,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "headstall and reins, with the bit and other appurtenances;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "like its Persian original,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "likaAmo", "text_ar": "لِكَامْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qar~aTa", "text_ar": "قَرَّطَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". It signifies The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "piece of iron in the mouth of the horse:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "thus, by extension, applied to"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "this with its thongs,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "straps, and apparatus:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "it comprises the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$akiymap", "text_ar": "شَكِيمَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which is the transverse piece of iron in the mouth; and the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faA^os", "text_ar": "فَاْس"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which is the piece of iron standing up in the mouth; and the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "misoHal", "text_ar": "مِسْحَل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which is the iron beneath the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hanak", "text_ar": "حَنَك"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xuT~aAfaAni", "text_ar": "خُطَّافَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which are two bent pieces of iron in the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "misoHal", "text_ar": "مِسْحَل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$kymp", "text_ar": "شكيمة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", on the right and left; and the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faraA$ataAni", "text_ar": "فَرَاشَتَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which are two pieces of iron wherewith are fastened the extremities of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ei*aAraAni", "text_ar": "عِذَارَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hakamap", "text_ar": "حَكَمَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which is the ring surrounding the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "marosain", "text_ar": "مَرْسَِن"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hanak", "text_ar": "حَنَك"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", of silver or iron or thong. (IDrd, in his Book on the Saddle and Bridle.)       -A2-  See"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lujomahN", "text_ar": "لُجْمَهٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "."}], "source_refs": []}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}